                        <div class="text">MODERN FARMING</div>
                        <p>Modern farming is a way of growing our food using advanced tools and clever ideas. Farmers use big machines like tractors to plant seeds and gather crops quickly. They also give special food to the soil, called fertilizers, to help plants grow strong. Sometimes, bugs can harm the crops, so farmers use special chemicals called pesticides to protect them. In some places, there's not enough rain, so farmers bring water to their fields with hoses and pipes, which is called irrigation. They also switch the crops they grow to keep the soil healthy. Some farmers even grow plants in special houses called greenhouses to protect them from bad weather. Computers and GPS help farmers know exactly what their crops need. There are also ways to farm without synthetic chemicals, called organic farming, and ways to do it without hurting the environment, called sustainable farming. Modern farming helps make sure we have lots of good food while taking care of the Earth..</p>
